250 g Ground Beef
1 tbsp Harissa Spice Blend
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
¼ cup Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit Lemon
80 g Tomato
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Baby Spinach
½ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.Wash and dry all produce. Zest, then juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges. Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.Cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces. Add peppers, half the Harissa Spice Blend and 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) to one side of a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside.

Add breadcrumbs, Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend, remaining Harissa Spice Blend and half the feta to a medium bowl. (TIP: If you prefer more tender patties, add an egg to the mixture!) Add beef, then combine.Form beef mixture into two 4-inch-wide patties (four patties for 4 ppl).

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then patties. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, cook patties in 2 batches, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.) Pan-fry until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side. Transfer patties to other side of the baking sheet with peppers. Roast in the middle of the oven until peppers are tender and patties are cooked through, 10-12 min.**

Meanwhile, add mayo, lemon zest and 1/2 tsp lemon juice (dbl for 4 ppl) to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add 2 tsp lemon juice and 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl both for 4 ppl) to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (TIP: Add a pinch of sugar to the dressing, if desired!)Add tomatoes and spinach, then toss to combine.

Divide patties, peppers and salad between plates. Sprinkle remaining feta over salad. Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.Serve lemon mayo alongside for dipping.